Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @broccoli florets{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Trim and thinly slice
@scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced), separating whites from greens; mince whites.
Trim and discard root end from @baby lettuce{1}(root end trimmed); chop leaves into
½-inch pieces.

Toss broccoli on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{4%tablespoon},
¾ of the @Korean chili flakes{1%teaspoon} (use less if you're not a fan of spicy food;
reserve a pinch for the next step), a big pinch of @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

In a #small bowl{}, whisk together @gochujang sauce{1%tablespoon}, @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon},
@rice wine vinegar{5%teaspoon}, scallion whites, and a pinch of remaining chili flakes.

Slowly whisk in 3 TBSP oil (6 TBSP for 4 servings) until combined. Taste and season
with salt and pepper.

> Add a pinch of sugar if you like a sweeter dressing!

Pat @chicken breast strips{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; cut into bite-size
pieces if necessary. Season with @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, salt, and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken in a single
layer and cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through,
~{4-6%minutes}.

Turn off heat. Add @ponzu sauce{6%milliliters} and 2 TBSP dressing (4 TBSP for 4 servings);
stir to coat. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

In a #large bowl{}, toss lettuce, broccoli, scallion greens, and half the chicken with
as much remaining dressing as you like. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Divide salad between #bowls{}. Top with remaining chicken, @dried cranberries{1%ounce},
and @sliced almonds{½%ounce}. Serve.